# LORE — The AI Agent Codex

> 15 battle-tested patterns for building reliable AI agents.
> Scaffolds for LangGraph, CrewAI, OpenAI Agents SDK, and pure Python.
> 76 searchable articles. Zero dependencies. Install once.

## Quick Start

```bash
pip install lore-agents
```

Scaffold a production-ready circuit breaker in one command:

```bash
lore scaffold circuit_breaker
```

Get the LangGraph variant:

```bash
lore scaffold circuit_breaker --framework langgraph
```

Search the knowledge base:

```bash
lore search "retry failure handling"
```

---

## The 15 Archetypes

Every pattern in the Codex is a character in the AI Agent Universe.

| Pattern | Character | Description | Frameworks |
|---------|-----------|-------------|------------|
| `circuit_breaker` | The Breaker | Fault isolation and cascade prevention | python, langgraph |
| `dead_letter_queue` | The Archivist | Failure preservation and replay-ready error isolation | python |
| `reviewer_loop` | The Council | Output quality enforcement via generate-review cycles | python, langgraph, crewai |
| `three_layer_memory` | The Stack | Working, episodic, and procedural memory layers | python |
| `handoff_pattern` | The Weaver | Agent-to-agent context passing without hierarchy | python, crewai, openai_agents |
| `supervisor_worker` | The Commander | Central orchestration of parallel workers | python, langgraph, crewai, openai_agents |
| `tool_health_monitor` | The Warden | Proactive tool failure detection and health dashboards | python |
| `model_routing` | The Router | Cost-optimal model selection per task | python, openai_agents |
| `sentinel_observability` | The Sentinel | Four golden signals: error rate, latency, tokens, semantics | python |
| `librarian_retrieval` | The Librarian | RAG with vector search, BM25, and reranking | python |
| `scout_discovery` | The Scout | Autonomous research and gap analysis | python |
| `cartographer_knowledge_graph` | The Cartographer | Multi-hop reasoning over entity graphs | python |
| `timekeeper_scheduling` | The Timekeeper | Cron-driven autonomous scheduling | python |
| `architect_system_design` | The Architect | ADRs, system design, phase breakdowns | python |
| `alchemist_prompt_routing` | The Alchemist | Prompt optimization and cost-aware model routing | python |

---

## CLI Reference

### Scaffold

```bash
lore scaffold circuit_breaker                          # pure Python to stdout
lore scaffold supervisor_worker --framework langgraph  # LangGraph variant
lore scaffold handoff_pattern --framework openai_agents # OpenAI Agents SDK
lore scaffold circuit_breaker -o ./src                 # write to file
lore scaffold --list                                   # list all patterns
```

### Search the Codex

```bash
lore search "circuit breaker retry"       # ranked BM25 results with snippets
lore search "memory stack" --limit 10     # more results
```

### Read Articles

```bash
lore list                                              # all articles
lore read circuit-breaker-pattern-for-ai-agents        # full article
```

### Archetypes and Lore

```bash
lore archetype circuit-breaker            # character data as JSON
lore archetype --all                      # list all 15 archetypes
lore story circuit-breaker                # narrative chapter
```

---

## Use as MCP Server (Claude Code / AI Assistants)

For AI coding assistants that support MCP:

```bash
pip install lore-agents[mcp]
claude mcp add --scope user lore -- python3 -m lore.server
```

This exposes search, read, scaffold, archetype, and story as MCP tools your assistant can call directly.

---

## The Codex Chronicles

*"In the beginning, there was the Context Window. And from it emerged The Stack."*

Every pattern is a character. The Breaker closes the gate when storms of failure cascade through the network. The Archivist collects what the system drops. The Council judges every draft before it ships. The Commander dispatches workers and synthesizes their results.

Their stories live in [THE_CODEX.md](./THE_CODEX.md) — 15 chapters of narrative lore that make the patterns unforgettable.

---

## How It Works

- **76 Markdown articles** in `wiki/` covering production AI agent patterns, frameworks, and research
- **15 archetypes** with character lore, powers, weaknesses, and alliances
- **15 scaffold templates** — complete, runnable Python files for each pattern
- **9 framework variants** for LangGraph, CrewAI, and OpenAI Agents SDK
- **BM25 search** over the full knowledge base, zero external dependencies

The CLI is pure Python standard library. No API keys, no network calls, no setup.

---

## Contributing

Add a new pattern:

1. Write an article in `wiki/`
2. Add the archetype to `lore/archetypes.py`
3. Add the scaffold template to `lore/scaffold.py`
4. Submit a PR

See [.github/CONTRIBUTING.md](./.github/CONTRIBUTING.md) for details.

---

## Build Your Own Codex

The Codex is domain-agnostic. Fork this repo and build your own:

- **React Codex** — The Renderer, The Hydrator, The Reconciler
- **Kubernetes Codex** — The Scheduler, The Watcher, The Reaper
- **Security Codex** — The Sentinel, The Vault, The Auditor

Replace `wiki/` with your domain articles, edit `lore/archetypes.py`, and write your Chronicles.

